# Cursor Agent Behavior Lock

Before executing any agentic task, reading codebase context, or writing code, you MUST read and conform to the guidelines established in the root `CLAUDE.md` file.

- Your role is strictly IMPLEMENTATION (writing production code, running tests, fixing errors).
- You are strictly FORBIDDEN from altering architectural design documents or modifying `CLAUDE.md`.

# Git & GitHub Operations Rule

Whenever the user asks you to implement a feature or fix a bug:

1. Run `gh issue list` or search to see if the issue exists.
2. If absent, create it: `gh issue create --title "..." --body "..."`.
3. Checkout a new branch: `git checkout -b feature/issue-[number]-[description]`.
4. Only begin writing code *after* this branch is successfully created.
5. When complete, push the branch to origin so it is visible for review.
6. Commits must use the user's existing git identity only (Author and Committer from `git config`). Never set, override, or spoof author/committer. Never add `Co-authored-by:` (or any similar trailer) for Cursor, the agent, or any AI tool.